						<summary>

						<p>These are fragments of some Kannaḍa inscriptions in early characters. One of them refers to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Madurekōṇḍa Kōpa</hi>•••••••• and to a case of self immolation by an individual by means of <hi rend="italic">khaṇḍasphuṭita</hi> (mutilation of flesh ?). The second piece mentions a tank built for (?) one•••• Kēsarīśvaradēva, and the third refers to Vīra-Pāṇḍya-Iḷaṅgōvēḷār ruling at Koḍumbāḷūr, Vikrama•••••••• dēva and to one Māramaseṭṭi.</p>						

						</summary>
